[I] A class for types that can be converted to a hash value

[T] Defines a class, Hashable, for types that can be converted to a hash value.
[T] This class exists for the benefit of hashing-based data structures. The package
[T] provides instances for basic types and a way to combine hash values.

[U] http://github.com/haskell-unordered-containers/hashable

